<Docs title="Skills" description="Specialized instruction sets loaded on demand for specific task types.">
  <h1>Skills Reference</h1>
  <p>Skills are markdown instruction files that provide specialized guidance for specific task types. They're loaded on demand when the agent detects a matching task pattern.</p>

  <h2>Available Skills</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Skill</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><strong>cleave</strong></td><td>Task decomposition, code assessment, and OpenSpec integration. Parallel execution via <code>/cleave</code>, code review via <code>/assess</code>.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>git</strong></td><td>Conventional commits, semantic versioning, branch naming, tagging, changelogs, and release workflow.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>oci</strong></td><td>Containerfile authoring, multi-arch builds, registry auth, image tagging, security scanning.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>openspec</strong></td><td>OpenSpec lifecycle commands and conventions for spec-driven development.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>pi-extensions</strong></td><td>Extension API reference — registerCommand, registerTool, event handlers, UI context.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>pi-tui</strong></td><td>TUI component patterns — Component interface, overlays, keyboard handling, theming.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>python</strong></td><td>Project setup (pyproject.toml, src/ layout), testing (pytest), linting (ruff), type checking (mypy).</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>rust</strong></td><td>Cargo project setup, testing, clippy, rustfmt, CI/CD, and Zellij WASM plugin development.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>security</strong></td><td>Input escaping, injection prevention, path traversal, process safety, secrets management.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>style</strong></td><td>Alpharius color system, typography, spacing, and semantic palette for visual consistency.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>typescript</strong></td><td>Strict typing, async patterns, error handling, Node.js API usage, node:test conventions.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>vault</strong></td><td>Obsidian-compatible markdown conventions for human-readable knowledge bases.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>How Skills Work</h2>
  <p>Skills are stored in <code>skills/&lt;name&gt;/SKILL.md</code>. The agent loads a skill file when it detects a matching task pattern. Skills provide:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Conventions and best practices for the specific domain</li>
    <li>Required tool configurations and flags</li>
    <li>Common pitfalls and error patterns to avoid</li>
    <li>Testing requirements and verification steps</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Skills are injected into the agent's context on demand — they don't consume context budget when not relevant to the current task.</p>
</Docs>
